title: Headers Whisper
Challenge Description: 
Our internal network monitors flagged an unusual spike in ICMP traffic between two developer workstations last night. While the packet volume was low, the timing was highly irregular.
We’ve captured a snippet of the conversation in the attached PCAP. On the surface, it’s just a series of pings. But N-Corp doesn't pay its engineers to spend all night pinging each other. Look closer

